name=\"graeme morrison\" />\n*[[Phil Godman]]<ref name=\"phil godman\">{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/stewart_s_melville_v_edinburgh_academy_godman_recalls_fond_memories_as_schools_gear_up_for_brewin_final_1_1503934 |title=Stewart's Melville v Edinburgh Academy: Godman recalls fond memories as schools gear up for Brewin final |newspaper=The Scotsman |date=4 March 2011 |accessdate=1 November 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Ruaridh Jackson]]<ref name=\"ruaridh jackson\">{{cite web |url=http://www.scotlandrugbyteam.org/content/view/208/86/ |title=Scotland Squad |publisher=Scottish Rugby |year=2012 |accessdate=1 November 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Graeme Morrison]]<ref name=\"graeme morrison\">{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/rugby/top_rugby_stories/dollar_crash_to_on_form_fettes_in_cup_thriller_1_524198 |title=Dollar crash to on-form Fettes in cup thriller |newspaper=The Scotsman |date=8 March 2001 |accessdate=3 November 2012}}</ref> \n*[[Gregor Townsend]]<ref name=\"1989 final\" />\n*[[Richie Vernon]]<ref name=\"richie vernon\">{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/2354412/Dundees-tall-order-to-halt-top-Dollar.html |title=Dundee's tall order to halt top Dollar |publisher=The Daily Telegraph (London) |date=27 January 2005 |accessdate=3 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.schoolsrugby.co.uk/ Schools Rugby website]\n* [http://www.scottishrugby.org/schools-cup-competitions-201718 Scottish Rugby website]\n\n{{Rugby union in Scotland}}\n\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1983]]\n[[Category:School sport in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Rugby union competitions in Scotland|Schools' Cup]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Scottish Rugby Schools' Cup''' is the annual [[Scotland|Scottish]] schools' [[rugby union]] cup competition.<ref name=\"scottish rugby\">{{cite web |url=http://www.scottishrugby.org/schools-cup-competitions |title=Schools' Cup Competitions |publisher=Scottish Rugby |year=2015 |accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref>  Competitions are held at under 18 and under 16 age group levels and are organised by [[Scottish Rugby Union|Scottish Rugby]].<ref name=\"scottish rugby\" />  The finals are held at [[Murrayfield Stadium]] in [[Edinburgh]].<ref name=\"scottish rugby\" />\n\nThe competitions have had many different formats over the years.  For season 2019-20 there are four competitions for each age group: The Cup, The Shield, The Plate and The Bowl.<ref name=\"scottish rugby\" />  The main cup competitions involve a straight knock-out format.<ref name=\"scottish rugby 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.scottishrugby.org/news/13/09/03/state-school-entry-surge-cup-competition |title=State School Entry Surge for Cup Competition |publisher=Scottish Rugby |year=2013 |accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref>  In 2013-14 a new shield competition was introduced for those teams eliminated in the preliminary and first rounds of the cup competitions.<ref name=\"scottish rugby\" />\n\nThe fixtures and results are regularly posted on the Scottish Rugby website and in the mainstream media.  Previous sponsors include the [[Bank of Scotland]], Bell Lawrie White and [[Brewin Dolphin]].\n\n==U18 Cup==\n'''Key:'''\n{|class=\"wikitable\" \n|bgcolor=\"#CEDFF2\"|Match tied - cup shared\n|-\n|}\nThe inaugural competition took place from the start of the 1983\u201384 season.<ref name=\"rugby record\" />\n\nPrior to the 1997\u201398 season most [[Independent school (United Kingdom)|Independent schools]] did not participate in the U18 Cup.\n\nWinners of the U18 Cup competition include:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Season !! Winner !! Score !! Runner-up\n|-\n| 1983-84 || [[North Berwick High School]] || 6-0 || [[Marr College]]<ref name=\"rugby record\">{{cite book|title=Rugby Record|publisher=Scottish Rugby|year=2012|page=471}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1984-85 || [[Galashiels Academy]] || 21-9  || [[Dunblane high school#Dunblane High School|Dunblane High School]]<ref name=\"1985 final\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thesouthernreporter.co.uk/lifestyle/different-sports-for-different-sorts-1-3588407 |title=Different sports for different sorts? |publisher=[[Southern Reporter (newspaper)|Southern Reporter]] |date=2 November 2014 |accessdate=22 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1985-86 || [[Galashiels Academy]] || 10-0 || [[Dunblane high school#Dunblane High School|Dunblane High School]]<ref name=\"1986 final\">{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19860326&id=JbxAAAAAIBAJ&sjid=w6UMAAAAIBAJ&pg=6627,6762105 |title=Schools cup is retained by Gala |newspaper=[[The Herald (Glasgow)]] |date=26 March 1986 |accessdate=2 November 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1986-87 || [[Kelso High School (Scotland)|Kelso High School]] ||  || [[Dunblane high school#Dunblane High School|Dunblane High School]]<ref name=\"rugby record\" />\n|-\n| 1987-88 || [[Galashiels Academy]] ||  || [[St Aloysius' College, Glasgow|St Aloysius' College]]<ref name=\"rugby record\" />\n|-\n| 1988-89 || [[St Aloysius' College, Glasgow|St Aloysius' College]] || 16-0 || [[Galashiels Academy]]<ref name=\"1989 final\">{{cite web |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19890316&id=ODNAAAAAIBAJ&sjidMlkMAAAAibaj&pg=3328,4990158 |title=College gain revenge with cup win |publisher=The Herald |date=16 March  1989 |accessdate=2 November 2012}}</ref> \n|-\n| 1989-90 || [[St Aloysius' College, Glasgow|St Aloysius' College]] || 19-15 || [[Galashiels Academy]]<ref name=\"1990 final\">{{cite web |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/spl/aberdeen/college-retain-trophy-1.585131 |title=College retain trophy |publisher=The Herald |date=22 March 1990 |accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1990-91 || [[Galashiels Academy]] ||  || [[St Aloysius' College, Glasgow|St Aloysius' College]]<ref name=\"rugby record\" /> \n|-\n| 1991-92 || [[Marr College]]<ref name=\"rugby record\" /> ||  ||\n|-\n| 1992-93 || [[St Aloysius' College, Glasgow|St Aloysius' College]]<ref name=\"rugby record\" 